article.headline: Navy 70, Lafayette 63
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Greg Sprink scored 29 points and Navy made eight of 10 shots from the line in the final minutes for a 70-63 victory over Lafayette on Saturday. Kaleo Kina added 10 points for the Midshipmen (13-12, 3-7 Patriot League). Matt Betley had his second double-double against Navy, finishing with 16 points and 10 rebounds for Lafayette (8-17, 2-8). Bilal Abdullah added 13 points and nine rebounds, and Andrew Brown added 11 points, six rebounds and six assists. Lafayette charged to an early 10-point lead before Navy got back into contention with a 19-3 run. Spring scored the Midshipmen's last seven points of the first half and Navy took a 35-28 lead into the break. Abdullah dropped in a layup that capped a 13-5 run and pulled Lafayette within 55-53 with 5:16 left in the game. Navy took control with a seven-point run and shot 8-for-10 from the line down the stretch to seal the win.
